}
```

Explain the function of this code fragment in the context of generating a web page.

A fragment of a client-side script is provided below. This script is used to estimate the reading time of a news summary provided by the user in a text area.

```javascript
function getStats(content) {
    let words = content.trim().split(/\s+/);
    let count = words.length;
    let speed = 200; // average words per minute
    let time = Math.ceil(count / speed);

    let result = "Count: " + count + " | Time: " + time + " min";
    return result;
}

// Event listener for form submission
let form = document.getElementById('summaryForm');
form.onsubmit = function(event) {
    event.preventDefault();
    let userText = document.getElementById('summaryBox').value;
    let stats = getStats(userText);
    document.getElementById('display').innerHTML = stats;
};
```

Describe the processing that occurs when the user enters the text `"The web is an evolving ecosystem of interconnected data."` into the text area (id: `summaryBox`) and clicks the submit button.

